      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1097">
               <p>A native of <placeName>Placey, Northumberland</placeName>, Hunter was awakened in
                  his later teens by the preaching of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1065.xml"
                     />Christopher Hopper</persName>. He eventually began to preach locally, and in
                     <date when="1767">1767</date> was persuaded to enter the <seg ana="itinerancy"
                     >itinerant</seg> ministry (see <hi rend="italic">Works</hi>, 10:343). Hunter
                  served faithfully, mainly in the north of <placeName>England</placeName> and
                     <placeName>Scotland</placeName>, until retiring from travelling in <date
                     when="1794">1794</date>. He continued to preach locally until his death. See
                     <hi rend="italic">AM</hi> 2 (<date when="1779">1779</date>): 589–98; <hi
                     rend="italic">EMP</hi>, 2:240–61; and <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi>
                  (post-Wesley, <date when="1798">1798</date>), 1:413–14.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
